The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Tuesday, August 03, 2004 				 Medal for Telegraph
																								The Telegraph has won a third consecutive honour for the quality of its printing with the worlds leading organisation of newspaper and media publishing, IFRA, awarding it a gold medal.																								After passing stringent tests that included critical evaluation of sample copies from the daily production, the newspaper has also been made a member of an exclusive international club  the first from India.																								Earlier, the newspaper had bagged an award presented by IFRA Asia and a certificate from the Newspaper Association of America in international acknowledgement of the quality of its printing. The Telegraph is the only newspaper outside America to have received this certificate.																								At a recent ceremony in Washington, it was awarded the IFRA gold medal and honoured with membership of the International Newspaper Colour Quality Club for 2004-06. Some 180 newspaper titles from 34 countries had enrolled for the 10-year-old competition. 
